  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison was welcomed by anti-slavery friends at Isaac Post&apos;s house. On Saturday, Garrison left for Syracuse. Samuel Joseph May is looking better than expected, but he is lacking in vigor. May has made up his mind to go to Europe. May&apos;s daughter, Mrs. Charlotte Wilkinson has a beautiful baby. Samuel J. May will be in Boston on Friday or Saturday. On Saturday evening, Garrison spoke on the religious aspects of &quot;our cause&quot; in the church in Cortland, where W. H. Fish officiates. Garrison also gave three long speeches on &quot;Inspiration, the Bible, Ancient and Modern Tests of Piety, and the relations of our cause to to the government and Union.&quot; Fish has done great work in this region.</subfield>
  </datafield>
